[[Image:Schefflerska palatset 2010b.JPG|thumb|300px|The Scheffler Palace.]]

The '''Scheffler Palace''' ({{lang-sv|Schefflerska palatset}}), commonly known as the '''Haunted Mansion''' (''Spökslottet''), is a [[mansion]] located at [[Drottninggatan, Stockholm|Drottninggatan]] 116 in [[Stockholm]], [[Sweden]]. The mansion, which was built in the 1690s by the merchant [[Hans Petter Scheffler]], is the most famous, so called "[[haunted house]]" in Stockholm. Since the 1920s, the estate is owned by [[Stockholm University]] and mostly used for storage of art and to occasionally hold conferences.

