{{Multiple issues| {{autobiography|date=March 2016}}{{notability|Biographies|date=March 2016}}}} {{Infobox clergy | name = Tim Clark | birth_name = David Timothy Clark | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1968|12|31}} | education = [[B.A.]] [[Fresno Pacific University]], [[M.A.]] [[Vanguard University]] | occupation = [[Minister (Christianity)|Minister]], Author | spouse = Deborah | church = [[The Church on the Way|The Church On The Way]] | ordained = [[International Church of the Foursquare Gospel|Foursquare Church]] | writings = VIRAL | website = {{URL|http://pastortimclark.com}} }}
'''David Timothy Clark''' (Tim Clark) is an American pastor and author. Formerly Dean of Students at [[Life Pacific College]], he is now Senior Pastor of [[The Church on the Way|The Church On The Way]] in [[Van Nuys, California]]. In 2015, he published a [[devotional book]] on the [[Book of Acts]] called VIRAL.
==Biography== Born in 1968, Tim Clark was raised attending Florence Avenue Foursquare Church in [[Santa Fe Springs, California]]. After high school, he felt called to youth ministry while working at [[The Church On The Way]]. He later helped plant a church in [[Fresno, California]], received his bachelor's degree at [[Fresno Pacific University]], planted a church in Seattle, and pastored Newberg Foursquare Church in [[Newberg, Oregon]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Story|url=http://www.pastortimclark.com/?page_id=23|website=Fueled by Pastor Tim Clark|accessdate=2 March 2016}}</ref>
In 2007, Life Pacific College invited Clark to come on as Dean of Students, where he also served as adjunct professor and helped organize Lifehouse Foursquare Church in [[San Dimas, California]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Life Pacific College Academic Catalog 2012-2013|url=http://lpc-docs.s3.amazonaws.com/lpc_2012_2013_academic_catalog.pdf|accessdate=2 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Story|url=http://www.lifehousefoursquare.org/#/about-us/story|website=Lifehouse|accessdate=2 March 2016}}</ref> He received his master's degree from [[Vanguard University]] in 2010, and the following year he joined the Foursquare Church headquarters as Supervisor of the Greater Los Angeles District of Foursquare Churches.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tim Clark Named Supervisor of Greater L.A. District|url=http://www.foursquare.org/news/article/tim_clark_appointed_GLA_supervisor|website=The Foursquare Church|accessdate=2 March 2016}}</ref>
In 2013, the [[International Church of the Foursquare Gospel|Foursquare Church]] announced Clark would take the position as Senior Pastor of The Church On The Way.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tim Clark to Pastor The Church On The Way|url=http://www.foursquare.org/news/article/tim_clark_to_pastor_the_church_on_the_way|website=The Foursquare Church|accessdate=2 March 2016}}</ref> In 2015, he was invited to be a guest speaker at Converge 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=Speakers|url=http://www.converge15.org/converge15-speakers/|website=2015 Fall Leaders Conference|accessdate=2 March 2016}}</ref> He also published VIRAL, a 29-day devotional on the Book of Acts, to be made generally available in 2016.
==Personal life== Clark and his wife, Deborah, live with their three children in [[Los Angeles, California]].
